				<p>It&#8217;s important to think about semantic meaning here too. Consider using something like &#8220;callout&#8221; for a class name instead of &#8220;red&#8221;. That has more semantic meaning to the markup so that down the line if you decide to change the color for those elements, you won&#8217;t be stuck with a meaningless &#8220;red&#8221; describing them.</p>
